1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,412
This is what it feels like.

2
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:38,747
In just one day,

3
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:41,416
every dream you've built

4
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,835
can just disappear, son.

5
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:46,629
It feels so unfair, doesn't it?

6
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,810
But why are you pointing guns?

7
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,437
Preventing you to run away again.

8
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:13,782
<i>What information did Chiara get</i>
<i>after talking to Viktor?</i>

9
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,785
<i>And what information did she give Viktor?</i>

10
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:26,628
And to counter that plan,

11
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:28,755
we need a team focused solely on her.

12
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:44,354
That's what they're good at, right?

13
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:56,574
If she's still looking
for us, Mikoy and me,

14
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:57,700
if we're still her target,

15
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:01,204
we might as well get nearer to them.

16
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:04,624
In that way, the closer I get,

17
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:07,127
the easier it'll be for me
to figure out their next move.

18
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:10,004
Then your special task force

19
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:12,882
can focus on securing
and finding that bomb.

20
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,893
And mind you, it's also very expensive.

21
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:43,121
I know it's not enough, but

22
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:45,748
I think it's enough to get us started.

23
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:47,834
How did you get that much money?

24
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:56,175
<i>Inspired by the experts</i>
<i>in money laundering</i>

25
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:59,095
<i>and corruption, we will hide money</i>

26
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:04,100
<i>in seemingly unconventional places only.</i>

27
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:07,437
<i>We can't do online transactions,</i>

28
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,606
<i>because it can be traced easily.</i>

29
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:38,134
Here's what we talked about.

30
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,321
Even if we're struggling,

31
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:00,615
even if we've run out of budget,

32
00:04:00,698 --> 00:04:02,992
<i>we are trying to uphold</i>

33
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:06,371
the values and principles
of this organization.

34
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:37,360
Not one of my colleagues
has even checked on me.

35
00:04:38,736 --> 00:04:41,739
It's really hard being the good senator.

36
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,158
Meeting with the police.

37
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,577
Then another meeting with the president.

38
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:49,247
I'm exhausted.

39
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,041
Good thing

40
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:54,877
I have time to relax.

41
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,842
Thank you all.

42
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:03,761
Senator Quintin is living the life.

43
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:12,270
Honey, come on. Let's take a shower.

44
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:19,736
Come on. Go, go.

45
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:28,453
GENERAL RUIZ NORBERTO

46
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:50,767
Can't this matter wait
until tomorrow morning?

47
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:04,947
What is it now?

48
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:17,210
I'll tell my team to move double time.

49
00:06:17,293 --> 00:06:22,006
Sir, that's already the mandate
I've given the agency.

50
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:29,680
For the country, sir!

51
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:41,317
For the country.

52
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:45,905
<i>Senator Quintin has a special power</i>

53
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:49,075
<i>to access additional budget</i>
<i>for this operation?</i>

54
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:51,369
<i>Why he didn't tell me?</i>

55
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,621
<i>It's impossible for him to forget!</i>

56
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,562
And now you're so happy?

57
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,524
Because that witch left!

58
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:06,527
She's gone!

59
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:09,238
Before the sun even rose,
she packed up and left.

60
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,616
And please, please don't ever come back.

61
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:13,701
Please.

62
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:24,629
What gossip did you hear?

63
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:29,884
La Morte Bianca
blew up the Pinagpala family's bakery.

64
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:32,553
Even their house was blown up.

65
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:35,681
That witch is unbelievable!

66
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:36,766
Viktor!

67
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,142
My goodness!

68
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,978
How are our in-laws?

69
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,605
True to their names,

70
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:45,233
the Pinagpalas were blessed
to escape before the explosion.

71
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,361
Oh, thank God!

72
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:49,779
So,

73
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,365
where is Isabella now?

74
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,853
Mom, Dad.

75
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:26,983
I know you're having problems
with the bakery.

76
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,819
Sofie saw it on Fishbook.

77
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:31,445
That's how I found out.

78
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:35,950
I don't even know why
or what exactly happened.

79
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:41,706
I just hope you're all safe.

80
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:47,003
"I know you're trying
to keep me from worrying.

81
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:50,881
But that's impossible.

82
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:53,801
Because I love you both so much.

83
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:58,764
You're always on my mind.

84
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:03,144
I'm doing okay here.

85
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:07,773
The people are kind."

86
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:09,609
Let me, Mom.

87
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:15,072
"I hope you're doing okay.

88
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,366
And I hope

89
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:20,161
there's good news about Brother Mikoy too.

90
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:24,373
I pray for him every day.

91
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,918
I love you both so much."

92
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:31,130
Miss Tess!

93
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:34,592
- Mikoy!
- Mom, Mom.

94
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:37,136
Miss Tess!

95
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,181
Hello, Agent Sianong!

96
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:41,265
Miss Tess!

97
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:43,684
I just wanted to ask something.

98
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:45,186
Where's Sir Mario?

99
00:10:46,103 --> 00:10:47,271
Do you happen to know where Sir Mario is?

100
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,440
We haven't seen him since last night.

101
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,837
There. You see.

102
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:17,927
Agent Alex.

103
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:19,303
Do you want to work out?

104
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:21,597
No, maybe later. You guys go ahead.

105
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,973
- You need it more.
- Nice.

106
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:32,108
Lower down a little bit.

107
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:35,403
We need more stretching.

108
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,292
There.

109
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:54,505
Agent Alex.

110
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:56,424
Who are you looking for?

111
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:03,139
Where are you going?

112
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,517
- Where's she going?
- Exactly.

113
00:12:08,185 --> 00:12:09,812
Oh my goodness.

114
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:10,729
My goodness.

115
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,314
<i>You guys are unbelievable.</i>

116
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:30,166
What's this?

117
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:34,086
Did you know about
your father's plan to leave?

118
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,132
Mikoy.

119
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:42,761
Chiara?

120
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:46,182
Mario escaped?

121
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:51,437
Chiara, why aren't you wearing
your handcuffs again?

122
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:53,898
Are you planning to escape again?

123
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,526
Do I look like someone
who's about to escape?

124
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,491
I don't know why people
keep escaping this safe house.

125
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:07,328
Sweetheart, why did you
take off your handcuffs?

126
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:10,122
Agent Alex might get mad at us again.

127
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,625
Because I can't move properly.

128
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:21,467
Because you're under
the agency's immunity program, right?

129
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:28,557
Well, I'm not trying to escape anyway.

130
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:30,893
I just don't like wearing handcuffs.

131
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:34,021
Because I really can't move properly.

132
00:13:34,104 --> 00:13:36,148
It's not just about the handcuffs.

133
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:41,946
And let me remind you.

134
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:44,198
You're both under the immunity program.

135
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:46,659
We have a binding agreement.

136
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:50,120
So you're expected to cooperate
in exchange for protection.

137
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:55,000
So now, if you continue
refusing to cooperate,

138
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:57,127
we might as well revoke that.

139
00:13:57,711 --> 00:13:59,797
Come on, Alex. Don't do that!

140
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,382
We admit it.

141
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:03,926
Yes, we've made mistakes,
but we'll make up for them, okay?

142
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:08,847
Please don't revoke my family's immunity.

143
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:11,809
And sweetheart, we'll cooperate, okay?

144
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:12,893
Right?

145
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:18,566
We'll cooperate, if they're fair.

146
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:29,910
You're just not used

147
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,954
to being the one
who has to follow orders now.

148
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:34,665
That's right, Alex.

149
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:35,749
Let's start over.

150
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,835
Let's restart and refresh.

151
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,505
Just a reminder.

152
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:43,465
La Morte Bianca is in a hurry.

153
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:46,468
So we should be working
on our strategy too, right?

154
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:54,560
Why don't you explain to us
why your father escaped?

155
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:58,480
Sir Mario escaped?

156
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:01,233
Mikoy, did you know about this?

157
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:33,140
Bok, there's nothing.

158
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:36,393
I've checked every angle
of our CCTV cameras.

159
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:38,646
None of them captured Sir Mario leaving.

160
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,441
That's impossible.

161
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:45,611
What are we supposed
to tell General Norberto?

162
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:47,154
Let's just report it to him.

163
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:50,991
That all we have is a letter?

164
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:57,706
Just like you, I have
no idea why my father left

165
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,500
or where he went.

166
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:01,669
I swear, I really don't know.

167
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:13,138
Pretty amazing, huh?

168
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,933
Last night, one safe house member came in.

169
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:18,394
And now, one safe house member is out.

170
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,354
Mario is incredible.

171
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:23,816
The security here is so tight,
yet he still escaped?

172
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:27,820
I mean,
Mario is our neighborhood's top guy!

173
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:29,697
He's like Captain Barbell!

174
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:31,240
Tough as steel!

175
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:32,282
Wow!

176
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:35,786
No wonder he's amazing.
I wonder what Mario's background is.

177
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:41,500
I just heard that
when General Ruiz visited the bakery,

178
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:44,420
they used to serve together.

179
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:47,047
So, he was a soldier?

180
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:48,424
Or maybe a police officer?

181
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:51,051
Maybe he used to be
some kind of action hero.

182
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:53,387
The question is, where's Mario?

183
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,014
Maybe he's on a mission.

184
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:08,986
How did you sleep last night?

185
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:11,155
You know,

186
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:14,158
I missed sleeping beside you.

187
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:16,535
I didn't get much quality sleep.

188
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:19,788
But it's okay because
we're back to normal now.

189
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,001
Chiara.

190
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:28,505
What's with that tone, sweetheart?

191
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:32,259
I understand.

192
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:34,595
You and Alex just don't get along.

193
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,473
Or maybe

194
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:39,433
you're just too much alike.

195
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:44,229
If opposites attract, then you two…

196
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,734
That's it!

197
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:55,074
I'm the one caught in the middle
whenever you clash.

198
00:17:59,787 --> 00:18:02,081
It's not like that, sweetheart.

199
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:06,627
Given our situation
and the immunity the agency granted us,

200
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,129
we're the ones who need to make an effort.

201
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,881
We're the ones who need to adjust.

202
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,184
I know.

203
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:25,771
But you know, they trusted us, sweetheart.

204
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,107
They're taking a chance on us, Chiara.

205
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,566
And with everything we do,

206
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:33,153
they're seeing whether
we're truly worthy of that trust.

207
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:36,323
I mean, from their point of view,

208
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,534
we weren't even their allies at first.

209
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:39,535
And yet,

210
00:18:39,618 --> 00:18:42,746
they gave us a chance to help them.

211
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:45,457
That's a huge amount
of trust they've placed in us.

212
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:49,461
So it's only right that we protect it.

213
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:53,882
If you can, sweetheart,

214
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:56,468
just make a few more adjustments.

215
00:18:58,303 --> 00:18:59,972
Those agents

216
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:03,058
are under an incredible
amount of pressure.

217
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:07,062
Imagine receiving constant follow-ups
from your boss every single day.

218
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:10,023
Whose boss is also getting
constant follow-ups from above.

219
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:11,316
Right?

220
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,318
That's a lot of pressure.

221
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:17,406
So don't be so hard on Agent Alex.

222
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:29,001
I didn't know you were on Alex's team!

223
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:33,046
It's not like that, sweetheart!

224
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:37,426
It's just unfair that they're doing
everything they can to protect us,

225
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:38,760
and now,

226
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:43,056
my family and my friends
are under the immunity program too.

227
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:46,977
Then, are we going to repay them
by being difficult?

228
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:49,646
That doesn't seem right, does it?

229
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:55,944
I'm just asking

230
00:19:57,154 --> 00:20:00,657
that we focus on being helpful to them.

231
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:05,120
Let's not become
a headache for Alex and Sianong.

232
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,206
Sweetheart, in that way,

233
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:10,334
we can be sure we won't lose our immunity.

234
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:11,627
Right?

235
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:16,715
Chiara.

236
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:19,843
I can't afford to lose this immunity.

237
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:23,305
Especially now that
my family's involved too.

238
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:26,308
Chiara, we don't even have a home anymore.

239
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:28,268
Our bakery is gone too.

240
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:30,854
My father left.

241
00:20:31,605 --> 00:20:33,398
And I don't even know where he went.

242
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:36,193
This immunity is the only thing
I have left to rely on.

243
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,153
So please.

244
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:41,365
Can't you do this for me?

245
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:58,340
I know you lost more than just property.

246
00:20:58,423 --> 00:21:00,050
That's family treasure.

247
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:03,804
And believe me, it really pains me
to see you lose everything.

248
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:11,144
You didn't want this to happen.

249
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:15,065
I'm sorry. It's just hard sometimes.

250
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:19,736
Yes, we're all here
together in the safe house.

251
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:22,656
We don't even know
where La Morte Bianca is.

252
00:21:22,739 --> 00:21:27,202
For all we know,
she could be nearby. Right?

253
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:35,919
I also feel guilty.

254
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:39,172
But it's just frustrating.

255
00:21:41,883 --> 00:21:45,429
I know. I know, sweetheart.

256
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:47,764
You're not the only one
feeling frustrated.

257
00:21:47,848 --> 00:21:51,643
And if the pressure's getting too heavy,

258
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:57,024
there's always a way to ease the pressure.

259
00:22:01,194 --> 00:22:05,324
Seriously, you really know
how to charm me.

260
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:09,328
It's not just your laughter
I've won. I've won your heart too.

261
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:48,218
He's on emergency leave, sir.

262
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:06,361
That's rather suspicious.

263
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:37,184
I'm always worried.
Every minute. You know that.

264
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:43,940
Oh, well.

265
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:46,860
<i>But they're being</i>
<i>searched by La Morte Bianca.</i>

266
00:24:52,574 --> 00:24:54,367
Come on, tell me.

267
00:24:54,451 --> 00:24:56,161
Sir Mario escaped.

268
00:24:56,244 --> 00:24:59,289
Mario escaped? When?

269
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:01,333
Last night, before Chiara arrived.

270
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:02,792
Where would he go?

271
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:04,252
We really don't know, sir.

272
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:15,180
Wait, did you consult Agent Alex?

273
00:25:18,058 --> 00:25:20,435
We'll be in trouble.

274
00:25:21,895 --> 00:25:23,104
We're incomplete.

275
00:25:23,855 --> 00:25:25,398
Cocoy is not here.

276
00:25:25,482 --> 00:25:26,316
- Oh, right.
- See?

277
00:25:27,692 --> 00:25:29,527
Cocoy is missing?
